#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:76 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The methods to estimate the optimal number of bins are well founded in "
"literature, and are inspired by the choices R provides for histogram "
"visualisation. Note that having the number of bins proportional to "
":math:`n^{1/3}` is asymptotically optimal, which is why it appears in "
"most estimators. These are simply plug-in methods that give good starting"
" points for number of bins. In the equations below, :math:`h` is the "
"binwidth and :math:`n_h` is the number of bins. All estimators that "
"compute bin counts are recast to bin width using the `ptp` of the data. "
"The final bin count is obtained from ``np.round(np.ceil(range / h))``."
msgstr ""
"估计最优箱数的方法在文献中有充分的理论基础，并受到 R 语言中直方图可视化的"
"启发。注意，箱数与 :math:`n^{1/3}` 成比例在渐近意义上是最优的，这也是"
"为什么它出现在大多数估计器中的原因。这些只是插件方法，为箱数提供了良好的"
"起点。在以下方程中，:math:`h` 是箱宽，:math:`n_h` 是箱数。所有计算箱数的"
"估计器都会通过数据的 `ptp` 转换为箱宽。最终的箱数由 ``np.round(np.ceil("
"range / h))`` 得出。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:87 of
msgid "'auto' (maximum of the 'sturges' and 'fd' estimators)"
msgstr "'auto'（'sturges' 和 'fd' 估计器的最大值）"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:88 of
msgid ""
"A compromise to get a good value. For small datasets the Sturges value "
"will usually be chosen, while larger datasets will usually default to FD."
"  Avoids the overly conservative behaviour of FD and Sturges for small "
"and large datasets respectively. Switchover point is usually "
":math:`a.size \\approx 1000`."
msgstr ""
"一种折中方法以获得较好的值。对于小数据集通常会选择 Sturges 值，而大数据"
"集则默认使用 FD。这种方法避免了 FD 和 Sturges 在小数据集和大数据集上过于"
"保守的行为。切换点通常为 :math:`a.size \\approx 1000`。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:95 of
msgid ""
"h = 2 \\frac{IQR}{n^{1/3}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:97 of
msgid ""
"The binwidth is proportional to the interquartile range (IQR) and "
"inversely proportional to cube root of a.size. Can be too conservative "
"for small datasets, but is quite good for large datasets. The IQR is very"
" robust to outliers."
msgstr ""
"箱宽与四分位距（IQR）成正比，与 a.size 的立方根成反比。对于小数据集可能"
"过于保守，但对大数据集效果很好。IQR 对异常值非常稳健。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:103 of
msgid ""
"h = \\sigma \\sqrt[3]{\\frac{24 * \\sqrt{\\pi}}{n}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:105 of
msgid ""
"The binwidth is proportional to the standard deviation of the data and "
"inversely proportional to cube root of ``x.size``. Can be too "
"conservative for small datasets, but is quite good for large datasets. "
"The standard deviation is not very robust to outliers. Values are very "
"similar to the Freedman-Diaconis estimator in the absence of outliers."
msgstr ""
"箱宽与数据的标准差成正比，与 ``x.size`` 的立方根成反比。对小数据集可能"
"过于保守，但对大数据集效果不错。标准差对异常值不够稳健。在没有异常值的"
"情况下，其值与 Freedman-Diaconis 估计器非常相似。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:113 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"n_h = 2n^{1/3}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:115 of
msgid ""
"The number of bins is only proportional to cube root of ``a.size``. It "
"tends to overestimate the number of bins and it does not take into "
"account data variability."
msgstr ""
"箱数仅与 ``a.size`` 的立方根成正比。它倾向于高估箱数，且未考虑数据的"
"变异性。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:120 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"n_h = \\log _{2}n+1\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:122 of
msgid ""
"The number of bins is the base 2 log of ``a.size``.  This estimator "
"assumes normality of data and is too conservative for larger, non-normal "
"datasets. This is the default method in R's ``hist`` method."
msgstr ""
"箱数为 ``a.size`` 的以 2 为底的对数。该估计器假设数据服从正态分布，对于"
"较大且非正态的数据集过于保守。这是 R 语言中 ``hist`` 方法的默认方式。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:128 of
msgid ""
"n_h = 1 + \\log_{2}(n) +\n"
"            \\log_{2}(1 + \\frac{|g_1|}{\\sigma_{g_1}})\n"
"\n"
"g_1 = mean[(\\frac{x - \\mu}{\\sigma})^3]\n"
"\n"
"\\sigma_{g_1} = \\sqrt{\\frac{6(n - 2)}{(n + 1)(n + 3)}}"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:135 of
msgid ""
"An improved version of Sturges' formula that produces better estimates "
"for non-normal datasets. This estimator attempts to account for the skew "
"of the data."
msgstr ""
"Sturges 公式的改进版本，能为非正态数据集提供更好的估计。该估计器尝试考虑"
"数据的偏度。"

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:140 of
msgid ""
"n_h = \\sqrt n\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.statistics.histogram.histogram_bin_edges:142 of
msgid "The simplest and fastest estimator. Only takes into account the data size."
msgstr "最简单且最快的估计器。仅考虑数据大小。"

